   FBN-REFEREES (Undated) _ For the third time in 10 days, an NFL
game was decided by an apparently mistaken call by the referees,
the latest instance coming Sunday when the Jets were awarded a
last-gasp touchdown. The uproar over the bad calls _ which have had
a direct impact on various teams' playoff chances _ has the NFL
squirming and just about everyone calling for some kind of revival
of an instant-replay system. By Richard Sandomir.
