   FBN-PLAYOFFS (Undated) _ With three weeks to go, the NFL
postseason picture has a somewhat quirky look. In the NFC, a whole
bunch of sub-.500 teams are battling for the final wild-card spot.
Meanwhile, in the AFC, it is the Eastern Division that dominates.
If the playoffs began tomorrow, the AFC East would send four teams
_ the Jets, the Dolphins, the Bills and the Patriots _ with one of
them the division winner and the other three the wild-card teams.
By Bill Pennington.
