<P>
   BAXTER-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ The prevailing political explanation
for the latest mood swing toward impeachment, as the House
Judiciary Committee nears a vote, is that wavering Republicans have
been swayed by the argument that a vote to impeach will be
remembered by those who favor it, while a vote against will be
forgotten by those who oppose it. (Baxter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED MONDAY ON WASHINGTON WIRES.
