<P>
   TX-AUTO-INSURANCE _ Insurance Commissioner Elton Bomer sets the
benchmark auto rate, and for the second consecutive year, it's
going down _ 5.5 percent statewide. We explain what it means and
how it affects Central Texans. (Elizondo, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   INSURANCE _ After going to court to battle insurance companies
for the right to see individual company data, insurance analyst
Birny Birnbaum releases his analysis of the information. (Elizondo,
Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   GOV-BUSH-RELIGIOUS-VIEWS _ The Anti-Defamation League on Tuesday
was expected to release a copy of a letter Gov. George W. Bush
wrote last month clarifying his religious views. (Herman, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS _ Florida is ranked 3rd in the nation when it comes to
the number of truck-related fatalities, according to Citizens for
Reliable and Safe Highways. The activists group blames fatigued
truck drivers, but trucking industry types say most of the
accidents are caused by car drivers, not trucks. (Banstetter, Palm
Beach Post). 12.
</P>
<P>
   DOMESTIC-ABUSE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Sometimes, in the
shorthand people use when they have talked about something too many
times, Sandy will say, ``My husband kidnapped me and stabbed me and
tortured me and I almost died and God knows why I didn't.'' And
unless you already know the story, you think surely she must be
exaggerating. Because who on Earth could survive all that? This is
an incredibly emotional journey through one woman's life,
near-death and rebirth. (Evans, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
