<P>
   CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT (Washington) _ President Clinton has been
``misleading,'' ``evasive'' and even ``maddening,'' says White
House Special Counsel Gregory Craig at Clinton's impeachment
hearing. But try as they might, Republican members of the House
Judiciary Committee cannot get Craig to say the ``l'' word _ that
the president lied. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-STRATEGY (Washington) _ In the divided House Judiciary
Committee hearings, Republicans are mostly ignoring the theoretical
questions of what constitutes an impeachable offense to sharply
question the President Clinton's lawyers about whether he lied
under oath. Democrats, meanwhile, carp about the unfairness of the
process and try to support contentions that the president's
misdeeds don't warrant removal from office. By GREG McDONALD and
NANCY MATHIS.
</P>
