prepares to vote on whether to impeach the president, Rep. Mary
Bono, R-Calif., says she believes Clinton committed perjury and
ought to be removed from office. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   SOCIAL-SECURITY (Washington) _ Controversy over private
investment accounts dominates the opening of a two-day White House
conference on Social Security. President Clinton insists the system
``must remain a rock-solid guarantee'' that ``can be counted on
regardless of the ups and downs of the economy or the market.'' By
DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   SCOTUS-POLICE (Washington) _ A unanimous Supreme Court rules
that the Constitution forbids police officers from automatically
searching a driver and his or her car after making a stop for a
traffic violation. By STEVE LASH.
</P>
