<P>
   SCI-CLONE-JAPAN (Undated) _ Scientists in Japan announce that
they have produced eight calves cloned from an ordinary cell from
an adult cow, by a method they say has a far greater success rate
than those used so far. By Gina Kolata.
</P>
<P>
   CHECHNYA-KIDNAP (Moscow) _ The severed heads of four kidnapping
victims _ identified as three Britons and a New Zealander _ were
found Tuesday on the side of a road in Chechnya, the breakaway
region on Russia's southern border that emerged undefeated from a
brutal war two years ago only to be engulfed and isolated by a wave
of kidnappings and crime. By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON &LR;  (Will move in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH (Washington) _ The White House opened its final defense
of President Clinton before the House on Tuesday, addressing in far
greater detail than before the facts and issues of the impeachment
case against Clinton and adopting a more conciliatory tone in
testimony before the House Judiciary Committee. By John M. Broder.
</P>
<P>
   With photos.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-ASSESS (Washington) _ As Gregory M. Craig, the White
House special counsel led off President Clinton's defense Tuesday,
the audience that mattered was not the House Judiciary Committee.
Nor was it the national television viewers. It was 20 to 30
moderate Republicans, who can swing the House impeachment vote one
way or another. A news analysis. By Alison Mitchell.
</P>
