<P>
   &UR; IS THIS DIRTY? &LR;
</P>
<P>
   It's a beautiful warm spring day and Rodger and his wife, Ellie,
are at the zoo.
</P>
<P>
   Ellie's wearing a cute, loose fitting, pink spring dress,
sleeveless with straps. As they are walking through the ape exhibit
and pass in front of a very large gorilla, the gorilla goes ape. He
jumps up on the bars, holding on with one hand (and 2 feet),
grunting, and pounding his chest. He is obviously excited by Ellie
in the wavy dress.
</P>
<P>
   Rodger noticing the excitement, suggests that Ellie tease the
poor fellow. Rodger suggests Ellie pucker her lips, wiggle her
bottom, and play along. Hesitantly, Ellie does and Mr. Gorilla gets
even more excited, making noises that would wake the dead.
</P>
<P>
   Then Rodger suggests that Ellie let one of her straps fall,
which she does, and Mr. Gorilla is just about to tear the bars
down. `Now try hiking up your dress a little.''This drives the
gorilla absolutely crazy.
</P>
<P>
   Then, Rodger grabs Ellie, rips open the door to the cage, slings
her in with the gorilla and says `now, tell HIM you have a
headache.`
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Why Men Have it Better &LR;
</P>
<P>
   You can open all your own jars
</P>
<P>
   When clicking thru the channels you don't have to stop on every
shot of someone crying.
</P>
<P>
   You can leave a hotel room bed unmade
</P>
<P>
   You can kill your own food
</P>
<P>
   You see the humor in `Terms of Endearment`
</P>
<P>
   Your underwear costs $7.50 for a pack of 3
</P>
<P>
   None of your coworkers have the power to make you cry
</P>
<P>
   Chocolate is just another snack
</P>
<P>
   One mood, all the time
</P>
<P>
   The remote is yours and yours alone
</P>
<P>
   You need not pretend you're `freshening up` when you go to the
bathroom
</P>
<P>
   You think the idea of punting that small, ankle-biting dog is
funny
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DAVID LETTERMAN TOP TEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TOP TEN THINGS TO DO IN THE WHITE HOUSE WHEN HILLARY IS OUT OF
TOWN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   10. New sign: `If this Oval Office is rockin', don't bother
knockin'.`
</P>
<P>
   9. White House pool filled to brim with Jack Daniels.
</P>
<P>
   8. Clinton's pants fly at half mast.
</P>
<P>
   7. Huge kitchen fire when President attempts to microwave 30
pizzas at once.
</P>
<P>
   6. Lincoln Bedroom full of hookers wearing top hats and fake
beards.
</P>
<P>
   5. South Lawn suddenly strewn with cars up on blocks.
</P>
<P>
   4. White House renamed `Senor Bubba's Casa Del Amor.`
</P>
<P>
   3. Bill can finally indulge his passion for uncooked bacon.
</P>
<P>
   2. Every night, several rounds of `Oval Office Grab-Ass.`
</P>
<P>
   1. Three words: Inflatable Betsy Ross.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DAVID LETTERMAN TOP TEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Top Ten Cool Things About Having an Affair With the President &LR;
</P>
<P>
   10. At your request, nuclear launch code changed to `90210.`
</P>
<P>
   9.Your old job: beautician at strip mall. Your new job:
Secretary of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
   8.You now belong to a select group of 48,000 women.
</P>
<P>
   7.Allowed to drive the rarely-seen Presidential van.
</P>
<P>
   6.Get to pick up red phone and scream, `What's happenin', you
Russkie bastards?`
</P>
<P>
   5.You're the only college student to arrive at Spring Break in a
B1 bomber.
</P>
<P>
   4.Your name: Kate. Name of scandal: Kategate.
</P>
<P>
   3.According to Constitution, your 15-year-old brother
automatically becomes `First Dude.`
</P>
<P>
   2.Every morning, a delicious continental breakfast prepared by
Al Gore.
</P>
<P>
   1.50% off at all participating McDonald's.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DAVID-LETTERMAN TOP TEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Signs the Football Game You Are Watching Is Fixed'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   10. During the coin toss, a player calls ``heads'' and the ref
says, ``Yeah that's close enough''
</P>
<P>
   9. Instead of chanting ``We're 1,'' players chant, ``We're gonna
cover''
</P>
<P>
   8. John Elway has thrown five touchdown passes to the referee
</P>
<P>
   7. Referee only blows his whistle to get the attention of beer
vendor in the stands
</P>
<P>
   6. One team leaves the field after the 3rd quarter to ``beat the
traffic''
</P>
<P>
   5. TV coverage features the ``Budweiser Deliberate Fumble of the
Game''
</P>
<P>
   4. At the half they announce final score 21-17
</P>
<P>
   3. Name of winning team -- the Baltimore Bookies
</P>
<P>
   2. One team gets a fifth down ``for trying so hard''
</P>
<P>
   1. The New York Giants are winning
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GOOD BOSS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Smith goes to see his supervisor in the front office.
`Boss,` he says, `we're doing some heavy housecleaning at home
tomorrow, and my wife needs me to help with the attic and the
garage, moving and hauling stuff.`
</P>
<P>
   `We're shorthanded, Smith,` the boss replies. `I can't give you
the day off.`
</P>
<P>
   `Thanks, boss,` says Smith. `I knew I could count on you!`
</P>
<P>
   nn
</P>
