</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-LAWYERS _ Private lawyers who represented the state of
Texas in its tobacco lawsuit have asked for $6 billion to $25
billion in attorney's fees, according to a published report. That
compares with an original $2.5 billion fee, which was widely
criticized. Chasing confirmation and reaction. (McCarthy, Austin
American-Statesman).
