. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
MRFOX-STAGE (Los Angeles) _ As a kid growing up in New York, Tobias
Picker loved the fiction of Roald Dahl. But not Dahl's ``children's
books.'' Picker was drawn to Dahl's wicked humor in his adult short
fiction (the only kids' books Picker could stomach were A.A. Milne
and a bit of Dr. Seuss). That could make for a good match in
Picker's new opera, ``Fantastic Mr. Fox,'' based on a Roald Dahl
story, which opens at L.A. Opera Wednesday. By Reed Johnson. 
. 
AARON-ART (Los Angeles) _ Aaron Yamagata enjoys discussing his
passion for art. ``I get to speak to the world when I draw,'' says
the Encino resident. ``When I want harmony, happiness, peace, and
love, that's what I draw and that's my message to the world.'' By
Betty Kwong. 
. 
