<HEADER>
A9171 &Cx1f; tic-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR &LR;      12-08 0263
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, Dec. 9. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
CLINTON-RABIL (Chandler, Ariz.) - The Marine Corps reads reserve
Maj. Daniel Rabil of Chandler the riot act and busts him back to
the inactive list. Rabil is the guy who wrote the virulent
anti-Clinton editorial in the Washington Times a few weeks ago.
Even though he is still tacitly a Marines reserve, Rabil says his
career is over. By MARK SHAFFER. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BEN&AMP;JERRY (Phoenix) - The ice-cream entrepreneurs talk about
fighting off the Pillsbury doughboy, building a company with a
social conscience and whether you can go public and still keep the
passion. By JANE LARSON. Story will move in the ``F'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GOODYKOONTZ-COLUMN (Undated) _ Warren Miller has been making his
ski movies for 49 years. When it came to Phoenix recently, I
wondered: Who goes to these things? And why? By BILL GOODYKOONTZ.
Story will move in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
