NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, DECEMBER 9
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-TEXAS-EXECUTE-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Dec. 7,
about a death penalty appeal by a Canadian citizen in Texas
misstated the number of United States citizens now imprisoned in
foreign countries. It is 2,500, not 12,500.
</P>
<P>
   BC-REPRICED-OPTIONS-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Dec. 7,
about a new accounting rule for repricing stock options referred
incorrectly to the corporate affiliation of Yale Tauber, a
compensation consultant who was quoted about client interest in the
rule. He is a principal of William M. Mercer Inc. (Mercer
Management Consulting is a sister company.)
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-BATES-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 7)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of the dancer Peg Leg Bates sent by the New York
Times News Service on Monday, Dec. 7, misstated the name of his
surviving daughter. She is Melodye Bates-Holden of Kerhonkson,
N.Y., not Melodye Preston.
</P>
