<SLUG> BC-NETTER-HIRES-SUTRO-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NETTER DIGITAL HIRES SUTRO TO HELP WITH GROWTH PLANS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEN SULLIVAN  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Shares in Netter Digital Entertainment rose 38
percent on word that the company has retained an investment bank to
help it grow.
</P>
<P>
   The digital-effects and television production house, based in
North Hollywood, has hired Sutro &AMP; Co. to evaluate alternatives
such as establishing partnerships with other companies and raising
new capital to meet long-term growth plans, said Netter spokesman
Chad Kalebic.
</P>
<P>
   Netter, which produces the ``Babylon 5,'' ``Crusade'' and
``Voltron: The Third Dimension'' television programs, hopes among
other things to expand its 3-D and special-effects animation
services for the television, film and video-game industries.
</P>
<P>
   The company is growing. For its 1998 fiscal year ended June 30,
revenues were up 26 percent to $32.3 million. But the company's
sales are dependent on just a handful of projects, putting it in a
precarious position if one or two fall apart, said analyst Debra
Fiakas at HD Brous &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   ``Their projects tend to be big and can be subject to fits and
starts,'' she said. ``That isn't always conducive to promoting
consistency and a fully valued stock price.''
</P>
<P>
   Netter shares closed up 62.5 cents Tuesday at $2.25.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
