<SLUG> BC-DISNEY-PHILLY-SITE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PHILADELPHIA TO GET NEXT DISNEYQUEST THEME PARK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVE McNARY  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- The Walt Disney Co., underscoring its strategy of
diversifying its hugely successful theme parks, has decided to
expand its DisneyQuest indoor theme parks with a new site in
Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   The entertainment giant will announce today that it plans to
open a five-story, 80,000-square-foot facility in the City of
Brotherly Love by the summer of 2000. The first DisneyQuest opened
in Orlando, Fla., in June, and another under construction in
Chicago is set to open next summer.
</P>
<P>
   The decision to move ahead with the concept highlights Disney's
relentless pursuit of a broader customer base than the families
that flock to its theme parks in Florida, Southern California,
Japan and France. DisneyQuests include a gravity-defying virtual
roller coaster dubbed CyberSpace Mountain and a Virtual Jungle
Cruise on air-supported rafts paddled through roaring rivers and
surrounded by dinosaurs.
</P>
<P>
   Joe DiNunzio, vice president of Disney Imagineering, said the
Philadelphia facility will feature several attractions not seen in
Florida but retain the core concept. He also said the pace of
expansion might pick up beyond 2000.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're trying to build a national brand with a presence in
large metropolitan markets,'' he said. ``Florida's been a great
laboratory for us. We're being asked to look at additional sites,
so I think we will accelerate our expansion.''
</P>
<P>
   DiNunzio said customer reactions to the first DisneyQuest have
been high with CyberSpace Mountain and the Create Zone, a studio
area where customers can design their own attractions.
</P>
<P>
   Disney has broadened its portfolio of attractions in recent
years with the Club Disney play-park chain, a cruise line, Animal
Kingdom in Florida and the ESPN stores and restaurants. It is
building a California Adventure park in the parking lot at
Disneyland in Anaheim that is scheduled to open in 2001.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
