<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDINALS-INJURIES-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURED ENDS TAKE IT EASY AT PRACTICE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By LEE SHAPPELL  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Injured defensive ends Simeon Rice (bruised ribs) and Andre
Wadsworth (bruised calf) are expected to play Sunday at
Philadelphia, but they might spend little, if any, time on the
practice field, Coach Vince Tobin said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Even if the ends can play, the club will activate additional
defensive linemen to help get it through. Both starting tackles
will be out.
</P>
<P>
   Eric Swann had successful arthroscopic surgery on his right knee
Monday in Vail, Colo., by Dr. Richard Steadman, the Cardinals said.
Steadman did not return telephone calls asking for details of the
procedure.
</P>
<P>
   Swann, out for the season, is expected to be placed on injured
reserve. His roster spot likely will go to Mike Moten, a member of
the practice squad. Moten would provide depth. The starting
assignment goes to Rashod Swinger.
</P>
<P>
   The other tackle, Mark Smith (ankle), definitely is out for the
Eagles game and could miss the New Orleans game the next week. The
starting assignment goes to Bernard Wilson, a starter most of the
previous two seasons.
</P>
<P>
   Tobin said it is likely that rookie end Jomo Cousins, who has
been inactive, will be active this week to guard against recurrence
of injuries to Wadsworth or Rice. Carl Simpson also is available.
He can play inside or outside on the line.
</P>
<P>
   Injuries also are wreaking havoc with the linebackers. Mark
Maddox will get his second start in the middle because Ron McKinnon
(knee) is not ready. Outside, the club wants to see Tony McCombs
(toe) in practice before it is ready to pronounce him ready to
return to the lineup. If he can't, Patrick Sapp and Terry Irving
will play in his spot.
</P>
<P>
   Tobin has not ruled out rookie running back Michael Pittman, who
suffered a broken hand in last week's loss to the New York Giants.
Pittman has been a contributor on special teams and in
short-yardage rushing situations. Tobin said the level of pain and
the type of cast on Pittman's hand will be factors in whether he
can play. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
